                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1618" type="given" value="HARRIET"></interp>HARRIET REED</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to Mr. Henry Gooch, at Camberwell. I received this paper from the collector of the Vauxhall Water-works, for 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. due for water—the prisoner afterwards came—he said he had called for the water-rate—I asked if it was right—he said, "Yes, quite right"—I asked him to give me a receipt, or sign the bill—he said he could not write, bat he would put his cross—I believed he came from the collector, and had a right to come from him, for the rate, and I paid him the money on that belief, and he put his cross to this paper.</p>
